}, {\"sentence\": \"Chock full of fun facts, as well as eye-catching graphics and photography geared toward ages 7-12, the Kids Guide - free and downloadable - features all 39 Olympic sports and all 22 Paralympic sports captured in 110 pages.\", \"from\": 1273, \"to\": 1495, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1455, \"end\": 1472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paralympic sports\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_sports\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Chock\", \"from\": 1273, \"to\": 1278}, {\"ngram\": \"fun facts\", \"from\": 1287, \"to\": 1296}, {\"ngram\": \"eye-catching graphics\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1330}, {\"ngram\": \"photography\", \"from\": 1335, \"to\": 1346}, {\"ngram\": \"ages\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1365}, {\"ngram\": \"the Kids Guide - free and downloadable - features\", \"from\": 1372, \"to\": 1421}, {\"ngram\": \"all 39 Olympic sports\", \"from\": 1422, \"to\": 1443}, {\"ngram\": \"110 pages\", \"from\": 1485, \"to\": 1494}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each sport has its own page, which includes an introduction to the sport, facts and trivia, and athlete profiles.\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1609, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each sport\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1506}, {\"ngram\": \"its own page\", \"from\": 1511, \"to\": 1523}, {\"ngram\": \"an introduction\", \"from\": 1540, \"to\": 1555}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1568}, {\"ngram\": \"facts\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1575}, {\"ngram\": \"trivia\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1586}, {\"ngram\": \"athlete profiles\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1608}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The guide also includes various activities, like games and puzzles, coloring, quizzes and more, as well as information about how to watch NBCUniversal's coverage of the events.\", \"from\": 1610, \"to\": 1786, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1748, \"end\": 1760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.275604472520467e-14, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The guide\", \"from\": 1610, \"to\": 1619}, {\"ngram\": \"various activities\", \"from\": 1634, \"to\": 1652}, {\"ngram\": \"games\", \"from\": 1659, \"to\": 1664}, {\"ngram\": \"puzzles\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1676}, {\"ngram\": \"quizzes\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1695}, {\"ngram\": \"information\", \"from\": 1717, \"to\": 1728}, {\"ngram\": \"the events\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1785}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The guide provides families with the opportunity to discuss the history of the Olympic Games, including iconic symbols, origin of the Opening and Closing Ceremonies, and the promotion of clean and safe competition.\", \"from\": 1788, \"to\": 2002, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The guide\", \"from\": 1788, \"to\": 1797}, {\"ngram\": \"families\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 1815}, {\"ngram\": \"the opportunity\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1836}, {\"ngram\": \"the history\", \"from\": 1848, \"to\": 1859}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 1880}, {\"ngram\": \"iconic symbols\", \"from\": 1892, \"to\": 1906}, {\"ngram\": \"origin\", \"from\": 1908, \"to\": 1914}, {\"ngram\": \"the Opening and Closing Ceremonies\", \"from\": 1918, \"to\": 1952}, {\"ngram\": \"the promotion\", \"from\": 1958, \"to\": 1971}, {\"ngram\": \"clean and safe competition\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 2001}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Families will learn about the host city of Paris, also known as \\\"La Ville Lumi\\u00e8re\\\" - or \\\"The City of Light\\\" - and get introduced to the Olympic and Paralympic mascots.\", \"from\": 2003, \"to\": 2170, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2046, \"end\": 2051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.845347809891065e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Families\", \"from\": 2003, \"to\": 2011}, {\"ngram\": \"the host city\", \"from\": 2029, \"to\": 2042}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"La Ville Lumi\\u00e8re\", \"from\": 2067, \"to\": 2084}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"The City\", \"from\": 2091, \"to\": 2100}, {\"ngram\": \"Light\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2109}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic and Paralympic mascots\", \"from\": 2135, \"to\": 2169}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SportsEngine, part of the NBC Sports Next portfolio of brands, is a leading provider of technology for youth and amateur sports, helping clubs, leagues and teams better manage their activities through easy-to-use technology platforms.\", \"from\": 2172, \"to\": 2406, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2172, \"end\": 2184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports_Group\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"SportsEngine\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports_Group\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 2186, \"to\": 2190}, {\"ngram\": \"the NBC Sports\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2208}, {\"ngram\": \"Next portfolio\", \"from\": 2209, \"to\": 2223}, {\"ngram\": \"brands\", \"from\": 2227, \"to\": 2233}, {\"ngram\": \"a leading provider\", \"from\": 2238, \"to\": 2256}, {\"ngram\": \"technology\", \"from\": 2260, \"to\": 2270}, {\"ngram\": \"youth and amateur sports\", \"from\": 2275, \"to\": 2299}, {\"ngram\": \"helping clubs\", \"from\": 2301, \"to\": 2314}, {\"ngram\": \"leagues\", \"from\": 2316, \"to\": 2323}, {\"ngram\": \"teams\", \"from\": 2328, \"to\": 2333}, {\"ngram\": \"their activities\", \"from\": 2348, \"to\": 2364}, {\"ngram\": \"easy-to-use technology platforms\", \"from\": 2373, \"to\": 2405}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SportsEngine Play was launched in October 2023 as the first subscription streaming service for youth and amateur sports, which also features a comprehensive library of player development and training content.\", \"from\": 2407, \"to\": 2615, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"SportsEngine Play\", \"from\": 2407, \"to\": 2424}, {\"ngram\": \"October\", \"from\": 2441, \"to\": 2448}, {\"ngram\": \"the first subscription streaming service\", \"from\": 2457, \"to\": 2497}, {\"ngram\": \"youth and amateur sports\", \"from\": 2502, \"to\": 2526}, {\"ngram\": \"a comprehensive library\", \"from\": 2548, \"to\": 2571}, {\"ngram\": \"player development\", \"from\": 2575, \"to\": 2593}, {\"ngram\": \"training content\", \"from\": 2598, \"to\": 2614}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NBC andPeacockwill be NBCUniversal's primary platforms for its coverage of the 2024 Paris Olympic Games, scheduled for July 26-Aug. 11, and the Paralympics, which will take place Aug. 28-Sept. 8.\", \"from\": 2617, \"to\": 2812, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2617, \"end\": 2620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999999925562406, \"rank\": 7.439264000270516e-09, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 2639, \"end\": 2651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.275604472520467e-14, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its coverage\", \"from\": 2676, \"to\": 2688}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Paris Olympic Games\", \"from\": 2692, \"to\": 2720}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 2736, \"to\": 2740}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paralympics\", \"from\": 2757, \"to\": 2772}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 2790, \"to\": 2795}, {\"ngram\": \"Sept.\", \"from\": 2804, \"to\": 2809}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peacock will feature live coverage of all events, all NBC programming, replays, clips and more, the most comprehensive Olympics streaming destination in U.S. media history, which will provide families with ample opportunities to follow along with the Kids Guide.\", \"from\": 2813, \"to\": 3075, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Peacock\", \"from\": 2813, \"to\": 2820}, {\"ngram\": \"live coverage\", \"from\": 2834, \"to\": 2847}, {\"ngram\": \"all events\", \"from\": 2851, \"to\": 2861}, {\"ngram\": \"the most comprehensive Olympics streaming destination\", \"from\": 2909, \"to\": 2962}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S. media history\", \"from\": 2966, \"to\": 2984}, {\"ngram\": \"families\", \"from\": 3005, \"to\": 3013}, {\"ngram\": \"ample opportunities\", \"from\": 3019, \"to\": 3038}, {\"ngram\": \"the Kids Guide\", \"from\": 3060, \"to\": 3074}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NBC and Peacock will present live coverage of the Opening Ceremony on Friday, July 26, beginning at noon ET.\", \"from\": 3077, \"to\": 3185, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3077, \"end\": 3080, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999999925562406, \"rank\": 7.439264000270516e-09, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 3085, \"end\": 3092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.7865957652562672e-12, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}, {\"begin\": 3127, \"end\": 3143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9985744249334398, \"rank\": 0.0007225257578413277, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"